Patch summary:
Set release aconfig defaults needed by the desktop build. Quick Settings stays
on the known-good non-Compose path because the desktop QS customizations target
the classic implementation, including the tile removals and panel interaction
behavior used by this VM.

This also enables Launcher3 desktop visual-effect flags in the generated
release flag sets. Keeping those values here makes the behavior reproducible
across both trunk staging and BP4A-style builds instead of depending on runtime
flag edits after first boot.

diff --git a/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/blurred_home_animation_flag_values.textproto b/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/blurred_home_animation_flag_values.textproto
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/blurred_home_animation_flag_values.textproto
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+flag_value {
+  package: "com.android.launcher3"
+  name: "blurred_home_animation"
+  state: ENABLED
+  permission: READ_ONLY
+}
diff --git a/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/enable_overview_desktop_tile_wallpaper_background_flag_values.textproto b/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/enable_overview_desktop_tile_wallpaper_background_flag_values.textproto
